      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOIs in validation activities must directly correspond to absolute hemolysis index used in the COU decision; surrogate QOIs require documented mapping.",
      "rationale": "Validation used normalized hemolysis index (NIH) while COU requires absolute plasma-free hemoglobin concentration. Mapping between metrics documented but introduces additional uncertainty. Achieved level 3 versus required level 4."
